In [22]:
# Creating pivot table using Pandas
statewise = pd.pivot_table(covid_df, values = ["Confirmed","Cured","Deaths", "Active_cases"], index = "State/UnionTerritory" ,aggfunc = "max")
In [23]:
# Adding new column and finding the Recover rate
statewise ['Recovery Rate'] = statewise ["Cured"]*100/statewise["Confirmed"]
In [24]:
# Adding new column and finding the Mortality rate
statewise ['Mortality Rate'] = statewise ["Deaths"]*100/statewise["Confirmed"]
In [25]:
# Sorting the values based on the confirmed cases column
# Sorting descending order
statewise = statewise.sort_values(by = "Confirmed", ascending = False)

# Creating DataFrame
covid_df = pd.DataFrame(statewise)
# Calculate correlation matrix
correlation_matrix = covid_df[['Confirmed', 'Cured', 'Deaths', 'Recovery Rate', 'Mortality Rate']].corr()

# Visualize correlation matrix as a heatmap
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 8))
sns.heatmap(correlation_matrix, annot=True, cmap='coolwarm', vmin=-1, vmax=1)
plt.title('Correlation Matrix')
plt.show()

# Top 10 states with most active cases
top_10_active_cases = (
    covid_df.groupby(by="State/UnionTerritory")
    .max()[['Active_cases']]
    .reset_index()
    .sort_values(by='Active_cases', ascending=False)
    .iloc[:10]  # Select top 10 states
)

# Top 10 states with most deaths
top_10_states_with_most_deaths = (
    covid_df.groupby(by="State/UnionTerritory")
    .max()[['Deaths']]
    .reset_index()
    .sort_values(by='Deaths', ascending=False)
    .iloc[:10]  # Select top 10 states
)

# Top 10 states with most cured cases
top_10_cured_cases = (
    covid_df.groupby(by="State/UnionTerritory")
    .max()[['Cured']]
    .reset_index()
    .sort_values(by='Cured', ascending=False)
    .iloc[:10]  # Select top 10 states
)

# Create a figure and axes for each plot
fig1, ax1 = plt.subplots(figsize=(16, 7))
sns.barplot(
    data=top_10_active_cases,
    x="State/UnionTerritory",
    y="Active_cases",
    hue="State/UnionTerritory",
    palette=sns.color_palette('ocean', 10),  # Using a color palette with 10 different colors
    ax=ax1
)

ax1.set_xlabel("States")
ax1.set_ylabel("Active Cases")
ax1.tick_params(axis='x', rotation=45)  # Rotate x-axis labels directly with tick_params
plt.show()
